# SEED Block Cipher — Pure Simple Implementation
#
# 128-bit symmetric block cipher, 128-bit key, 16-round Feistel network.
# Standardised by KISA (Korea Information Security Agency).
#
# Reference: RFC 4269 — The SEED Encryption Algorithm
#   https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc4269
#
# Exposed API:
#   seed_encrypt_block(key: [u8], block: [u8]) -> [u8]
#   seed_decrypt_block(key: [u8], block: [u8]) -> [u8]
#
# No SFFI/Rust FFI — pure Simple, suitable for baremetal.

# ============================================================================
# S-Boxes — RFC 4269 Appendix A.1
# ============================================================================

